The paper deals with higher type computation and the theory of exhaustible and searchable sets, which are concepts related to computability and topology. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves the construction of selection and quantification functionals, which are related to programming languages and semantics, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the Cantor space and computable images, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves a topological characterization of compact subsets of function spaces, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
